        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 8 at 7:50PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 749 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Clemmons, or 9 miles west of Winston-Salem, moving southeast at 15
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Winston-Salem, Lexington, Clemmons, Bermuda Run, Huntsville,
Lewisville, Arcadia, Welcome, and Sedge Garden.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
